    LerpFloat
    LerpFloat is a utility class for linear interpolation of float values.

    Lerp time (speed) is a value greater than 0, less than or equal to 1, where a lower number is a slower lerp.

    Consider the speed parameter a multiplier of the divisor applied when calculating the difference between the target and the current, which is applied to the translation.

    If no speed is provided in the constructor, the default value of 0.25f will be applied to interpolations which don't hae a speed defined.
    LerpValue<T>
    LerpValue is a utility class for linear interpolation of numerical values.

    Lerp time (speed) is a value greater than 0, less than or equal to 1, where a lower number is a slower lerp.

    Consider the speed parameter a multiplier of the divisor applied when calculating the difference between the target and the current, which is applied to the translation.

    If no speed is provided in the constructor, the default value of 0.25f will be applied to interpolations which don't have a speed defined.
